{"title": "Middle Eastern Coalition", "content": "A frequent occurrence in 20 Minutes into the Future settings, especially those with some version of The War on Terror. A strange coalition that seems to consist of most Islamic and/or Arab nations or just of numerous terrorist organizations (often themselves funded by a Western Ancient Conspiracy of some sort) excluding Pakistan, Turkey and Iran. (Sometimes, writers who don't know better have Shia, Persian Iran uniting with Arab Sunni states like Saudi Arabia.note Whom the Iranian government detests more than the West.note Never mind Ibadi Oman.)\n\nThis seems to often be used as a strange version of an Anonymous Ringer for nations like Iran, Saudi Arabia, Libya and other Southwest Asian or Middle Eastern states.\n\nPrior to the 1980s, these tended to be secular military dictatorships or socialist/nationalist regimes (like the real-life abortive attempt to set up a United Arab Republic combining Egypt, Syria and Iraq, as well as Libya's attempt). Since the rise in fundamentalism, the Iranian Revolution and especially 9/11, a more popular idea is to combine it into one huge poorly defined \"Inevitable Caliphate\" theocracy. This is al-Qaida's and ISIL's primary war aim, but it is probably not in the stars \u2014 at least not if Iran and Turkey have anything to say about it. Beyond that, al-Qaida and ISIL are, at the end of the day, lunatic fringes; most other Islamists are non-violent nationalists who probably have a worse view of Osama bin Laden than most Westerners (\"You're making us all look evil!\" is what they usually say), and al-Qaida itself\u2014according to the CIA, MI6, French Intelligence, Russian Intelligence, and pretty much everyone else\u2014is down to about 300 guys on the run in the mountains of Pakistan and Yemen.\n\nIsrael's state with this power around is rarely mentioned. If Persians and Arabs are being conflated, there's often no mention of what the Kurds or Turks think of all this, and the Arab Christian population is \u2014 er, wait, there are Arab Christians?\n\nOften portrayed as a sort of Spiritual Successor to Red Scare, for fairly obvious reasons on the writers' part. May or may not be a Qurac.\n\nCompare United Europe and Expanded States of America. Contrast Balkanize Me. See also Space-Filling Empire.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MiddleEasternCoalition", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Americathon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/EndersShadow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ShadowPuppets", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBigOne", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WildCards", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HBeamPiper", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DarkFuture", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TomKratman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Caliphate", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Illium", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/StarCarrier", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WolfishNature", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/VladimirVasilyev", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Victoria", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LegacyOfTheAldenata", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLastCrusade", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/InTheYear2050AmericasReligiousCivilWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/IraTabankin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/Syfy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheOuterLimits1995", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/WitchCraft", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/BattlefieldEvolution", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Shadowrun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/GURPS", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/TranshumanSpace", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/FullThrust", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/StarGruntII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Battlefield", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ProjectReality", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BattlefieldBadCompany", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/UFOAlienInvasion", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HeartsOfIronII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Tropico", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoG